 ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":50,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":59,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":94,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger de Malherbe was born about 1165, in Tacolneston, Norfolk, England, his father, John de Malherbe II, was 32 and his mother, Matilda FitzSwain, was 31. He had at least 1 daughter with Olive fitz Alan."},"et":{"about 1165–":"umbes 1165–Surnud","1160–1207":"1160–1207","1165–Male":"1165–Surnud","1175–1216":"1175–1216","1178–1246":"1178–1246","1164–1236":"1164–1236","1167–Female":"1167–Surnud","1135–1181":"1135–1181","1136–1181":"1136–1181","1165":"1165","1164":"1164","1175":"1175","1160":"1160","1181":"1181","1216":"1216","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","1224":"1224","1136":"1136","1246":"1246","11